                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-339-off1744 t18300916-339-crimeloc1747"></join>. On the 4th of August these shoes hung against my window; I saw the prisoner come and cut them, or with a book take them off - I pursued him, and cried Stop thief! he threw them over Mr. Farmer's gate, in St. John-street; Waddington took him; as we brought him back Mr. Farmer brought out the shoes, and gave them to us.</p>
